                <Activity ProgramAndActivitiesId="438" SortOrder="1">
                    <Heading/>
                    <Details>
                        <Detail SortOrder="1" TypeOfProgramAndActivitiesDetailsId="656">
                            <FooterDetails>
                                <Email/>
                                <Footer/>
                                <WebAddress>http://www.iaf.gov/about-the-iaf/at-a-glance-3798</WebAddress>
                            </FooterDetails>
                            <Heading/>
                            <Paragraph>The Inter-American Foundation (IAF) was created in 1969 (22
                                U.S.C. 290f) as an experimental U.S. foreign assistance program. The
                                Foundation is governed by a nine-person Board of Directors whom the
                                President appoints with the advice and consent of the Senate. Six
                                members are drawn from the private sector and three from the Federal
                                Government. The Board of Directors appoints the president of the
                                Foundation.</Paragraph>
                        </Detail>
                        <Detail SortOrder="2" TypeOfProgramAndActivitiesDetailsId="657">
                            <FooterDetails>
                                <Email/>
                                <Footer/>
                                <WebAddress>http://www.iaf.gov/about-the-iaf/more-about-the-iaf</WebAddress>
                            </FooterDetails>
                            <Heading/>
                            <Paragraph>In Latin America and the Caribbean, the IAF promotes
                                equitable, participatory, and sustainable self-help development by
                                awarding grants and giving other technical assistance directly to
                                local organizations throughout the region. It also partners with the
                                public and private sectors to build support and to mobilize local,
                                national, and international resources for grassroots
                                development.</Paragraph>
                        </Detail>
                    </Details>
                </Activity>
            </ProgramAndActivity>
        </ProgramAndActivities>
